{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"552decae-351f-44a2-9a0a-e0075997869a","content":"**Yes, C# fully supports `stackalloc`'d `Span<nint>` and `Span<nuint>`.** Both compiled and ran without issues:\n\n```\nnint span:  0, 10, 20, 30\nnuint span: 0, 20, 40, 60\nnint size:  8 bytes        (on this 64-bit system)\n```\n\nThe only gotcha: `sizeof(nint)` requires an `unsafe` context because `nint`/`nuint` don't have a fixed predefined size (they're pointer-sized — 4 bytes on 32-bit, 8 bytes on 64-bit). But `stackalloc` itself works fine in a safe context when assigned directly to a `Span<T>`.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"9020ff6c-4ac9-49e5-a0d2-81b7561b3c03","outputTokens":186,"requestId":"1FC4:20D256:17E8793:1B0A968:69FE857A"},"id":"5e8bc29c-daa5-48a4-92f9-f92c5180fec2","timestamp":"2026-05-09T00:53:19.719Z","parentId":"b6e60ebb-72f7-4e49-a9e0-b6164f65bf7e"}
